Definition.WordDefinition:
Princess \Prin"cess\, n. [F. princesse. See {Prince}, and cf. {Princesse}.] 1. A female prince; a woman having sovereign power, or the rank of a prince. --Dryden. [1913 Webster]
So excellent a princess as the present queen. --Swift. [1913 Webster]
2. The daughter of a sovereign; a female member of a royal family. --Shak. [1913 Webster]
3. The consort of a prince; as, the princess of Wales. [1913 Webster]
{Princess royal}, the eldest daughter of a sovereign. [1913 Webster]
princess n : a female member of a royal family other than the queen (especially the daughter of a sovereign)
